-- KBR first-quarter net income slightly up
-- 
-- Fri May 4, 2007 7:00am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/04/us-kbr-results-idUSWNAS976920070504

 

 (Reuters) - Engineering and construction services firm KBR Inc. ( KBR.N ) reported a marginally higher net income for the first quarter. 

 The company, which was spun off from parent Halliburton Co. ( HAL.N ) last month, said its net income rose to $28 million, or 17 cents a share, from $26 million, or 19 cents a share, a year earlier. Earnings from continuing operations was 18 cents a share, compared with 15 cents a share a year ago, the company said. Consolidated revenue was $2.3 billion, slightly higher than the $2.2 billion it posted a year ago. Analysts on average expected earnings of 24 cents a share, before special items, for the latest first quarter, on revenue of $2,253.4 million. (Reporting by Aniruddha Basu in Bangalore)